{
  "texts": [
    "This, as we've argued, is the wrong metaphor.",
    "The machines are not trying to communicate something they believe or perceive.",
    "Their inaccuracy is not due to misperception or hallucination.",
    "A particularly surprising position is espoused by Fichte, who regards as lying not only lies of omission, but knowingly not correcting someone who is operating under a falsehood.",
    "For instance, if I was to wear a wig, and someone believed this to be my real hair, Fichte regards this as a lie, for which I am culpable."
  ]
}